{
  "stem": "13313.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Kasteelstraat, ?] Castle Street, because at the corner of the street, in the highway, there was an old castle, and a big piece of land and-- it was number 12-- it was right along the rail tracks.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Through our front window, we could see the tracks of the railroad from Brussels to Antwerp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were number 12. 12 [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Kasteelstraat ?] in Hove was the address.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For a few days we stayed with their relatives until-- until the-- the house was properly set up.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- I recall the first night that we were separated from my mother.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother gave her whatever kids belongings were, and then she found a place in Brussels, went in hiding herself, and then we then went to Hove.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that would have been, best of my recollection, I would say September of 1942, give or take.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Probably September 1942.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I remember saying goodbye.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember us taking the train, it was one train stop from another suburb called, [INAUDIBLE] it means, old god.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was another suburb-- there were stations along the-- for every village on the way, so it was one station stop from where we-- we-- we met to go to this place.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remember that the first night that we slept away from home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My brother was very, very-- he was much younger.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was-- he was-- he had just turned six years old, and I was-- I was three and 1/2 years older, so I was the protector, you see.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember when we went into that strange bed in that strange house of these, of the relatives of the Roggemans, my brother asked me, he says, Paul, when are we gonna see Mother again?",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When are we gonna go home again?",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
